of the other cabins.

19:03.679 --> 19:04.923
You two are my guests.

19:04.947 --> 19:06.858
No, no, no, you take the master,

19:06.882 --> 19:08.960
we'll take one of
the smaller rooms. It's cool.

19:08.984 --> 19:10.750
There's two of you
and one of me,

19:10.986 --> 19:12.586
I'll take the cabin crew.

19:13.188 --> 19:14.554
Let's finish the tour.

19:25.868 --> 19:28.768
Oh, we've got our fishing poles
and life jackets in here.

19:29.238 --> 19:32.250
And, uh, at the aft of the boat
we got our zodiac,

19:32.274 --> 19:34.007
in case we run into any trouble.

19:34.610 --> 19:36.054
- What kind of trouble?
- [JOHN] You know,

19:36.078 --> 19:38.523
if we have to take the zodiac in
to one of the islands

19:38.547 --> 19:40.981
- for supplies.
- Supplies means beer.

19:42.918 --> 19:44.028
You guys ready?

19:44.052 --> 19:45.052
Yeah.

19:45.821 --> 19:47.131
Yeah, yeah, let's do this.

19:47.155 --> 19:49.189
All right, Coop,
you've got the bow line.

19:49.525 --> 19:51.035
It's a forward quarter line.

19:51.059 --> 19:52.826
And the midship line too.

19:53.795 --> 19:54.895
[CHUCKLES]

19:59.535 --> 20:01.167
Nothing but open water.

21:25.787 --> 21:27.020
Spooky isn't it?

21:28.824 --> 21:29.956
What's that?

21:32.127 --> 21:34.694
Out here all alone.

21:35.897 --> 21:36.897
Right.

21:38.333 --> 21:39.333
Where's Coop?

21:41.103 --> 21:42.636
