and have I mentioned to you
how smooth he was?

46:36.330 --> 46:39.242
He would call out "Bella"
and this nurse,

46:39.266 --> 46:41.611
she'd would run to him,
change his bandages,

46:41.635 --> 46:45.181
give him a sponge bath,
and Lord knows what else she did

46:45.205 --> 46:48.184
because whatever it was,
he started dreaming about her.

46:48.208 --> 46:50.487
And how I know this
is his bunkmates told him

46:50.511 --> 46:52.722
that in the middle of the night,
while he was dreaming,

46:52.746 --> 46:55.547
he would call out
"Bella-wood Bella-wood".

46:55.883 --> 46:57.916
So your grandmother's name
is Bella?

46:58.352 --> 46:59.596
- No.
- [VIVIAN] Oh.

46:59.620 --> 47:01.898
No. Look, my grandmother
was a saint,

47:01.922 --> 47:04.601
God rest her soul.
But I don't think my grandpa

47:04.625 --> 47:06.658
ever got over Bella. [CHUCKLES]

47:06.793 --> 47:08.371
Well, that's understandable.

47:08.395 --> 47:10.896
I mean, she was there for him
when he needed her most.

47:12.633 --> 47:14.344
- [JOHN] Yeah. Oh.
- [PHONE RINGS]

47:14.368 --> 47:16.501
[JOHN] Hey, looks like
we got service again.

47:16.770 --> 47:17.881
Hey, it's Sam.

47:17.905 --> 47:19.182
I gotta take this, guys.

47:19.206 --> 47:20.572
- [VIVIAN] Aw.
- Hey, Sam.

47:20.841 --> 47:22.807
That was such a sweet story.

47:24.244 --> 47:25.288
Really?

47:25.312 --> 47:27.406
I don't think it was sweet
for the nurse

47:27.430 --> 47:29.526
that had to change
the horny dude's bandages.

47:29.550 --> 47:31.516
- [LAUGHING]
- Stop being such a cynic.

48:15.596 --> 48:18.430
Viv, do you my have my, uh...

48:54.401 --> 48:56.946
- [COOPER] You want that?
- Ooh, wow. Instant refill.

48:56.970 --> 48:59.804
[VIVIAN LAUGHING]

49:00.907 --> 49:02.607
You guys want to play
cards again?

49:04.544 --> 49:06.411
Oh, fuck poker.

49:06.913 --> 49:08.813
I got a better idea.

49:10.050 --> 49:11.561
Truth or dare.

49:11.585 --> 49:13.263
Now I know you're really drunk.

49:13.287 --> 49:15.131
No, I'm serious.

49:15.155 --> 49:17.000
I haven't played that game
since like junior high.

49:17.024 --> 49:19.502
That doesn't matter,
you're still fucking brunettes

49:19.526 --> 49:21.471
and I can still hotwire
anything that moves.

49:21.495 --> 49:23.061
I haven't been hotwired yet.

49:23.497 --> 49:24.774
[COOPER] Are you sure
about that?

49:24.798 --> 49:26.698
Yeah, that's not what I heard
last night.

49:26.900 --> 49:29.045
- Gross, John.
- [JOHN] Yeah, you're telling me.

49:29.069 --> 49:31.347
It is gross, my virgin ears.

49:31.371 --> 49:32.681
No.

49:32.705 --> 49:34.017
God, Coop,
this is a really bad idea.

49:34.041 --> 49:35.818
Come on,
we haven't hung out like this

49:35.842 --> 49:37.287
since before my last tour.

49:37.311 --> 49:39.444
What's going on since then
and, hey,

49:39.646 --> 49:41.357
I want to hear a little bit more

49:41.381 --> 49:44.360
- about that Samantha chick.
- Oh, yeah. Fine, fine, fine.

49:44.384 --> 49:46.318
Oh. Oh, wow.

49:46.720 --> 49:48.765
- I don't even know how to play.
- Oh, it's okay.

49:48.789 --> 49:51.034
I'll break down the rules
for you, it's real simple.

49:51.058 --> 49:53.569
Whosoever asking the question
has complete control.

49:53.593 --> 49:54.904
No question is out
of the question,

49:54.928 --> 49:56.673
not even my time in the service,

49:56.697 --> 49:59.331
but you have to answer
truthfully.

50:00.400 --> 50:02.512
Oh, I can't believe
we're gonna do this.

50:02.536 --> 50:04.647
And if it's a dare,
you have to do the dare.

50:04.671 --> 50:06.316
That's it, that's the rules.

50:06.340 --> 50:07.784
All right, fine. Fine.

50:07.808 --> 50:09.741
- I'm in.
- [COOPER] Yes, we're doing it.

50:11.345 --> 50:12.610
Okay, you go first.

50:13.380 --> 50:14.612
It's your boat, you go first.

50:15.048 --> 50:16.114
Okay.

50:17.117 --> 50:18.416
Truth or dare?

50:18.652 --> 50:19.718
Truth.

50:20.921 --> 50:23.355
When did you lose
your virginity?

50:23.490 --> 50:24.556
Really?

50:24.758 --> 50:25.935
That's your fucking question?

50:25.959 --> 50:28.805
[JOHN MUMBLING]

50:28.829 --> 50:31.074
Hey, I don't know the answer
to that question.

50:31.098 --> 50:33.064
- Ah!
- [COOPER] Yes, you do.

50:33.700 --> 50:35.445
It was on our fourth date.

50:35.469 --> 50:38.114
Yeah, I don't think
that's you telling the truth.

50:38.138 --> 50:39.749
Well, it's not your question.

50:39.773 --> 50:41.551
- Well...
- [JOHN] I don't think

50:41.575 --> 50:42.618
that was the rules

50:42.642 --> 50:45.103
as they were explained to me.
You said "honesty."

50:45.127 --> 50:47.611
- [VIVIAN] Mm-hmm.
- I was 17 years old.

50:47.981 --> 50:49.147
[VIVIAN] With who?

50:49.750 --> 50:51.794
One question at a time, please.

50:51.818 --> 50:53.918
Okay, my turn, my turn.

50:54.554 --> 50:55.965
Truth or dare, Coop?

50:55.989 --> 50:57.055
Dare.

50:57.791 --> 50:58.901
Who with?

50:58.925 --> 51:00.136
[COOPER] I said dare.

51:00.160 --> 51:04.396
Okay. I dare you to tell me
who with, truthfully.

51:05.866 --> 51:09.501
Uh, some girl named Amanda.

51:09.803 --> 51:12.582
I played football
and she was a cheerleader

51:12.606 --> 51:16.441
and it was the American dream
kind of, not really.

51:18.011 --> 51:19.711
Amanda Matthews?

51:22.749 --> 51:24.527
One question.
No more questions.

51:24.551 --> 51:25.695
[VIVIAN SCOFFS] Amanda Ma...

51:25.719 --> 51:27.430
That is my babysitter!

51:27.454 --> 51:29.599
I mean, she didn't come
to my wedding...

51:29.623 --> 51:31.467
I mean, my wed... our wedding.

51:31.491 --> 51:32.969
It was a really long time

51:32.993 --> 51:34.470
before you and I met.

51:34.494 --> 51:35.827
How could you?

51:39.666 --> 51:41.243
Was it good?

51:41.267 --> 51:42.845
Was it... John, ask...
Your turn, ask a question.

51:42.869 --> 51:44.514
Me? I go again?

51:44.538 --> 51:46.582
John, don't do her any favors.

51:46.606 --> 51:48.440
Ask your own question.

51:49.075 --> 51:51.176
- Anything.
- I'm sorry, Viv.

51:53.180 --> 51:55.525
Did you kill anyone
in Afghanistan?

51:55.549 --> 51:56.592
[GROANS]

51:56.616 --> 51:58.561
- [CHUCKLES SARCASTICALLY]
- John, really, again?

51:58.585 --> 52:00.863
He said we could ask
any question

52:00.887 --> 52:03.132
even Afghanistan time.

52:03.156 --> 52:05.501
You are so fucking predictable.

52:05.525 --> 52:07.437
You do not have
to answer this question.

52:07.461 --> 52:09.572
[COOPER] No, it's okay,
I'll answer the question.

52:09.596 --> 52:12.008
It's only fitting
that the good doctor

52:12.032 --> 52:14.177
who is supposed
to be saving people's lives

52:14.201 --> 52:16.813
is so curious about
the other side of the equation.

52:16.837 --> 52:18.181
[VIVIAN] Coop. Really...

52:18.205 --> 52:19.849
[COOPER] I've been running
from those ghosts

52:19.873 --> 52:22.240
for a long time and I'm sick
of running from them.

52:22.843 --> 52:24.175
So that's a yes?

52:26.813 --> 52:28.112
Thirteen.

52:29.783 --> 52:31.149
Thirteen people?

52:41.695 --> 52:42.927
Truth or dare?

52:47.133 --> 52:48.199
Truth.

52:52.672 --> 52:54.172
How did you get through it?

53:01.581 --> 53:02.647
You.

53:04.851 --> 53:07.085
Knowing I was coming home
to you,

53:07.888 --> 53:09.120
to start a family.

53:10.957 --> 53:13.525
I never have to go back again
and be away from you.

53:21.868 --> 53:23.112
[COOPER] Is it my turn yet?

53:23.136 --> 53:26.682
I haven't even asked
a single question.

53:26.706 --> 53:27.706
[ALL CHUCKLE]

53:29.209 --> 53:30.675
[JOHN] Yeah, sure.

53:31.044 --> 53:33.177
Thank the Lord Jesus.

53:39.819 --> 53:42.687
Truth or dare...

53:43.089 --> 53:44.155
John?

53:47.727 --> 53:49.605
- Truth.
- [COOPER] Excellent choice.

53:49.629 --> 53:50.728
[JOHN] Dare.

53:51.698 --> 53:53.831
- Dare? Are you sure?
- Dare.

53:57.704 --> 53:59.771
I dare you...

54:00.840 --> 54:02.240
to kiss my wife.

54:03.043 --> 54:04.108
- What?
- [VIVIAN] What?

54:04.711 --> 54:05.855
You heard me.

54:05.879 --> 54:07.590
[VIVIAN] I'm not going
to kiss him.

54:07.614 --> 54:10.626
- [COOPER] Yes, he is.
- No, I am not gonna kiss her.

54:10.650 --> 54:12.617
Do I need to recap
the rules for you?

54:15.322 --> 54:16.721
Kiss her.

54:17.123 --> 54:19.201
This is so ridiculous.

54:19.225 --> 54:20.703
[COOPER] Come on.

54:20.727 --> 54:22.271
What's the big deal?

54:22.295 --> 54:24.662
It's not like it means anything,
right?

54:25.365 --> 54:27.599
- What?
- [COOPER] Kiss her.

54:28.168 --> 54:30.646
Kiss her.
Come on, John. Kiss her.

54:30.670 --> 54:32.070
Fine. Viv?

54:46.086 --> 54:48.086
It wasn't so hard, was it?

54:55.962 --> 54:57.261
Viv?

55:07.040 --> 55:09.641
Viv, come on.

55:12.712 --> 55:13.978
[VIVIAN] Go away.

55:14.714 --> 55:15.880
Viv?

55:19.386 --> 55:20.718
Viv?

55:22.956 --> 55:24.022
[LOCK RATTLES]

55:26.826 --> 55:27.959
Come on.

55:28.962 --> 55:30.339
What the hell is wrong with you?

55:30.363 --> 55:32.174
What the hell
is wrong with what?

55:32.198 --> 55:34.844
- With that that stupid game.
- I was just playing around.

55:34.868 --> 55:36.868
That... Yeah, it wasn't funny.

55:37.037 --> 55:38.814
It wasn't funny.

55:38.838 --> 55:41.205
Seriously,
what is wrong with you?

55:43.843 --> 55:45.109
[COOPER] I'm sorry.

55:47.347 --> 55:48.680
Stop.

55:49.282 --> 55:50.448
No.

56:02.095 --> 56:05.775
When we get home, I don't care,
you are taking your medicine.

56:05.799 --> 56:07.877
I am taking my medicine,
why don't you count it?

56:07.901 --> 56:10.012
I've seen you
throw them down the drain.

56:10.036 --> 56:11.369
I've seen it.

56:15.308 --> 56:18.242
I don't like the way
that it makes me feel.

56:18.745 --> 56:21.713
Well, I don't like
the way that you make me feel.

56:23.750 --> 56:28.097
I don't care if you take one
or if you take two

56:28.121 --> 56:30.399
or you take
the whole fucking bottle.

56:30.423 --> 56:33.257
Just replace this asshole
that's in front of me.

56:39.899 --> 56:41.132
[PILLS RATTLE]

57:13.967 --> 57:16.801
I don't know if I should be mad
at him or you.

57:40.493 --> 57:42.026
[INHALES DEEPLY]

58:01.014 --> 58:03.981
[GUNFIRE]

58:04.150 --> 58:07.251
[INDISTINCT YELLING]

58:07.854 --> 58:10.132
<i>[MAN] Parker,
get behind that bunker.</i>

58:10.156 --> 58:11.289
[GUN CLICKS]

58:12.225 --> 58:13.424
[EXPLOSION]

58:14.294 --> 58:17.328
[INDISTINCT YELLING]

58:23.903 --> 58:25.403
<i>[JOHN] Spooky, isn't it?</i>

58:49.362 --> 58:50.528
What's wrong?

58:51.464 --> 58:52.997
She won't start.

58:54.400 --> 58:55.444
What?

58:55.468 --> 58:59.582
<i>Bella won't start,
but that's okay</i>

58:59.606 --> 59:01.505
because you can hotwire
anything, right?

59:02.208 --> 59:04.920
No, no, I haven't hotwired
anything in 20 years

59:04.944 --> 59:06.544
and I sure as shit
never fixed a boat.

59:08.281 --> 59:09.925
Shouldn't be a difference.

59:09.949 --> 59:12.283
Here, help me out
in the engine room.

59:20.293 --> 59:22.538
Come on.
You've got to be kidding me.

59:22.562 --> 59:25.274
Oh, man. You said
you got a steal on this thing.

59:25.298 --> 59:26.575
How much you pay for it?

59:26.599 --> 59:28.266
You're not being helpful.

59:32.372 --> 59:33.748
Where's the radio?

59:33.772 --> 59:35.150
Attached to the computer,
so it's not working.

59:35.174 --> 59:36.485
Engine troubles?

59:36.509 --> 59:37.987
[JOHN] We think it's electrical.

59:38.011 --> 59:39.043
What about phones?

59:39.379 --> 59:40.379
No service.

59:41.147 --> 59:42.224
What does that mean?

59:42.248 --> 59:44.015
It means we're dead
in the water.

59:45.952 --> 59:47.151
But...

59:49.489 --> 59:51.589
John, do you have maps?

59:54.227 --> 59:56.272
[COOPER] What about a flare gun,
you got one of those?

59:56.296 --> 59:58.274
[JOHN] Flare guns,
check in there in the ottoman.

59:58.298 --> 59:59.697
See, the map's here.

01:00:02.468 --> 01:00:04.680
- Is your navigation working?
- [JOHN] It's dead.

01:00:04.704 --> 01:00:06.348
The whole computer system
is down.

01:00:06.372 --> 01:00:09.373
But these are all Pacific.
This is not gonna help us.

01:00:12.078 --> 01:00:13.344
[JOHN] I think...

01:00:13.479 --> 01:00:14.679
Where are we?

01:00:15.214 --> 01:00:16.525
I don't know, somewhere.

01:00:16.549 --> 01:00:19.317
Somewhere? That is not an answer
that I love.

01:00:20.553 --> 01:00:22.531
[JOHN] I think we're...
I think I found it.

01:00:22.555 --> 01:00:25.189
That's where we were,
so we're right around here.

01:00:25.525 --> 01:00:27.036
[COOPER] What's that?

01:00:27.060 --> 01:00:29.660
It's Rum Quay,
there's a supply station there.

01:00:30.163 --> 01:00:32.029
About how far do you think
this is?

01:00:32.398 --> 01:00:34.410
If I had to guess,
I'd say 15 miles.

01:00:34.434 --> 01:00:36.145
Fifteen miles north.

01:00:36.169 --> 01:00:38.035
Well, we could uh...

01:00:38.738 --> 01:00:40.471
The Zodiac.

01:00:41.641 --> 01:00:43.374
I'll take it, I'll go there.

01:00:43.576 --> 01:00:44.742
I'll get help.

01:00:45.111 --> 01:00:46.344
I'll help you pull it out.

01:00:53.453 --> 01:00:55.297
You can't just leave us here.

01:00:55.321 --> 01:00:57.066
We can't just stay here and hope

01:00:57.090 --> 01:00:58.500
that someone comes back
and finds us.

01:00:58.524 --> 01:01:00.124
Just take us with you.

01:01:00.326 --> 01:01:02.137
No, someone's gotta stay here
with the boat

01:01:02.161 --> 01:01:04.039
- in case they find it.
- Coop, come on.

01:01:04.063 --> 01:01:05.543
No, he's right,
somebody's gotta stay.

01:01:05.999 --> 01:01:07.042
I'll go.

01:01:07.066 --> 01:01:08.510
- [VIVIAN] What?
- What?

01:01:08.534 --> 01:01:10.434
No, man, this is...
It's my responsibility.

01:01:10.603 --> 01:01:12.003
David.

01:01:12.138 --> 01:01:13.237
David.

01:01:13.539 --> 01:01:14.984
Vivian, it's fine.

01:01:15.008 --> 01:01:16.418
I'm gonna take this thing
to the mainland,

01:01:16.442 --> 01:01:18.220
John's gotta stay here
and work on his boat...

01:01:18.244 --> 01:01:19.655
<i>And try to get Bella
back up and running</i>

01:01:19.679 --> 01:01:21.523
- and you'll get the help.
- [COOPER] Let's do it.

01:01:21.547 --> 01:01:23.748
John, can you just
give us a minute, please?

01:01:27.453 --> 01:01:28.764
Are you sure you wanna do this?

01:01:28.788 --> 01:01:30.421
I don't trust him to do it.

01:01:31.090 --> 01:01:33.424
- Look, about last night...
- No, I don't.

01:01:34.093 --> 01:01:36.560
- I love you.
- I love you.

01:01:38.264 --> 01:01:39.530
Here, hold this for me.

01:01:40.066 --> 01:01:41.432
Okay.

01:01:43.636 --> 01:01:45.136
Be careful.

01:01:46.105 --> 01:01:48.272
I survived fours tours
in Marjah.

01:01:48.541 --> 01:01:49.718
This will be cake.

01:01:49.742 --> 01:01:51.542
[ENGINE REVVING]

01:02:05.258 --> 01:02:07.124
Are you sure
he's gonna be all right?

01:02:08.327 --> 01:02:09.760
Of course he is.

01:02:13.633 --> 01:02:14.832
What's your deal?

01:02:15.234 --> 01:02:16.812
- What are you talking about?
- I don't know.

01:02:16.836 --> 01:02:18.602
You're just been acting
really...

01:02:18.805 --> 01:02:20.649
really strange.

01:02:20.673 --> 01:02:23.552
What, like pretending?

01:02:23.576 --> 01:02:25.609
I mean, we both have.

01:02:25.812 --> 01:02:27.489
What are you talking about?

01:02:27.513 --> 01:02:29.258
Viv, I mean, come on,
we gotta stop

01:02:29.282 --> 01:02:31.260
dancing around like this,
it's not fair to Coop.

01:02:31.284 --> 01:02:32.795
I'm not dancing
around anything, I...

01:02:32.819 --> 01:02:35.230
Oh, so you're not thinking
about what happened last August

01:02:35.254 --> 01:02:36.353
between us?

01:02:38.424 --> 01:02:41.270
Coop was right.
This is all making sense.

01:02:41.294 --> 01:02:43.539
I mean, why do you have this?

01:02:43.563 --> 01:02:45.629
Because we belong together.

01:03:14.627 --> 01:03:15.826
Here!

01:03:19.765 --> 01:03:22.244
[MAN] What are you doing
in the middle of the ocean

01:03:22.268 --> 01:03:23.601
in a rubber raft?

01:03:23.769 --> 01:03:25.603
We got some boat trouble.

01:03:26.739 --> 01:03:28.239
Who's "we"?

01:03:28.474 --> 01:03:30.552
Uh, there's a couple
of us a few miles back.

01:03:30.576 --> 01:03:32.409
All of our electric
just went out.

01:03:34.180 --> 01:03:35.813
You in the corps?

01:03:36.816 --> 01:03:38.883
Why do you say that?

01:03:40.219 --> 01:03:41.285
Your ink.

01:03:44.323 --> 01:03:45.656
[COOPER] You got a good eye.

01:03:48.194 --> 01:03:49.426
Twenty years in the Navy.

01:03:50.796 --> 01:03:51.929
[COOPER] All right.

01:03:52.498 --> 01:03:54.265
I'm glad to see you then.

01:03:54.467 --> 01:03:56.567
I was worried
you might be a pirate.

01:04:00.506 --> 01:04:02.840
You're not sporting a peg leg
back there, are you?

01:04:05.211 --> 01:04:07.222
No, but you know,
as a matter of fact,

01:04:07.246 --> 01:04:08.679
I've got a parrot.

01:04:10.449 --> 01:04:12.683
Your cell phone and your wallet.

01:04:14.420 --> 01:04:15.553
[GUN FIRES]

01:04:16.656 --> 01:04:18.189
Next one's in your leg.

01:04:26.532 --> 01:04:27.731
Now your wallet.

01:04:39.212 --> 01:04:40.444
Cooper.

01:04:43.583 --> 01:04:45.216
- [GUN FIRES]
- [GRUNTS]

01:04:59.298 --> 01:05:00.324
That's it?

01:05:00.348 --> 01:05:01.868
What, are you just
a one-bullet marine?

01:05:04.637 --> 01:05:05.948
Fucking jarhead.

01:05:05.972 --> 01:05:07.338
[FIRES GUN]

01:05:13.980 --> 01:05:16.592
John, I am married
to your best friend's brother.

01:05:16.616 --> 01:05:18.527
I mean, you have a girlfriend,
this is...

01:05:18.551 --> 01:05:22.620
Well, Sam's not really
a girlfriend.

01:05:30.763 --> 01:05:32.529
[ENGINE REVVING]

01:05:33.466 --> 01:05:35.244
<i>[VIVIAN] How could you do this?</i>

01:05:35.268 --> 01:05:36.445
You brought us on this boat.

